OL,4,CWhy so many Japanese children refuse to
OL,5,Cgo to school
OL,6, In Japan, more and more children are
OL,7, refusing to go to school, a phenomenon
OL,8, called "futoko". As the numbers keep
OL,9, rising, people are asking if it's a
OL,10, reflection of the school system, rather
OL,11, than a problem with the pupils
OL,12, themselves.
OL,14,FTen-year-old Yuta Ito waited until the
OL,15,Fannual Golden Week holiday last spring
OL,16,Fto tell his parents how he was feeling
OL,17,F- on a family day out he confessed that
OL,18,Fhe no longer wanted to go to school. 
